# Portfolio API Testing with REST Client
# Make sure your backend server is running on http://localhost:5000

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@authToken = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Admin Sign In (Run this first to get token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@sanyaportfolio.com",
  "password": "Admin@123456"
}

### 2. Get Profile (After login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Get All Education Records
GET {{baseUrl}}/education
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Create Education Record
POST {{baseUrl}}/education
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "institution": "Sample University",
  "degree": "Bachelor of Computer Science",
  "fieldOfStudy": "Computer Science",
  "startDate": "2020-09-01",
  "endDate": "2024-06-30",
  "isCurrentlyStudying": false,
  "grade": "First Class Honours",
  "percentage": 85.5,
  "description": "Specialized in web development and software engineering",
  "isVisible": true
}

### 5. Get All Projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Create New Project
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Portfolio Website",
  "description": "A modern responsive portfolio website built with React and Node.js, featuring admin dashboard, MongoDB integration, and authentication system.",
  "shortDescription": "Modern portfolio with admin dashboard",
  "category": "web-development",
  "technologies": ["React", "Node.js", "MongoDB", "Express", "JWT"],
  "features": ["Admin Dashboard", "Authentication", "CRUD Operations", "Responsive Design"],
  "links": {
    "live": "https://sanyabansal.com",
    "github": "https://github.com/sanyabansal115/portfolio",
    "demo": ""
  },
  "startDate": "2025-01-01",
  "endDate": "2025-11-19",
  "isCurrentlyWorking": false,
  "status": "completed",
  "isVisible": true,
  "isFeatured": true
}

### 7. Get All Contacts (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/contact
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 8. Create Contact Message (Public endpoint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "subject": "Project Inquiry",
  "message": "Hi Sanya, I'm interested in discussing a potential web development project. Could we schedule a call?",
  "phone": "+1-234-567-8900"
}